                </font></td>
                <td bgColor="#ECECEC"><textarea cols="48" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by GenmaTheMonk[/i]
[br]Feign death suspends you from the aggro list, with a slight chance to clear you from the aggro list.

If only a single mob is aggroed, and that mob does not naturally see through invis/itu, then being invis/itu when you stand will keep you in the 'suspended aggro' state as far as the mob is concerned.

If you are very far away when invis breaks, the mob may decide not to chase you and you then only have 'latent aggro' as far as the mob is concerned -- it may transfer aggro to other mobs if it social, and it may chase after you if you get within range.

There are a variety of tricks that can be used with this knowledge.

-- Genma, 65 Monk, Lanys T'Vyl
[/quote]</textarea><br /></td>
