                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/19/2003&nbsp;: 5:21:54 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> A short list of reasons why I love my CoS:<br /><br />1.  FD among non-wandering mobs that do not see invis (this is actually very common).  Stand and click CoS and walk away.  Great for quickly fixing raid wipes in which you are the only surviving member of the raid.  Zlandicar comes to mind.<br /><br />2.  Indirect agro pulling.  Root the mob next to the one you want.  Click CoS and run to the zone line.  When you get there, cast Darkness on your desired mob and then zone.  Come back and root DOT your mob.  This is the preferred way to farm a Vex Thal key Lucid Shard in Akheva Ruins.  That big agro radius for the Shaded Stones actually works in your favor.<br /><br />3.  Save a spell slot when you need to move around and cast frequently.  I still use Skin of Shadow when I travel but that CoS is so convenient I wind up clicking it a lot.<br /><br />4.  You screwed up big time and you have a bunch of angry mobs coming after you and need to run through a bunch more to get to the zone.  Chain click the CoS, keep running and don't look back.  No CoS?  Stun.  Splat.  Loading.  Please wait.<br /><br />5.  Instantly kill your pet!  Ok this is not actually a good thing.  Be carefull where you put your CoS key.<br /></span></font></td>
