                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/19/2003&nbsp;: 09:41:05 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Now that i am the proud owner of a pre nerf COS, i was wondering what were some of the benefits of the effect, other than the obvious.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote">Other than the obvious, there are no benefits to the pre-nerf CoS.  Insta-cast invisibility.<br /><br />The only real 'unique' use of the pre-nerf CoS I've seen, done, or heard about is the ability to pull a mob through other mobs without aggroing.  I've personally never had the need to use it this way, but would expect it to require the pull through mobs not see invis and don't naturally assist the aggroed mob ...very rare instances. <br /><br />Several times, I've heard that you can literally lose agro with it by FDing, then hitting it when you stand back up (providing again that the mob doesn't see through invis) ...but I have never ever ever EVER had the pre-nerf CoS work that way for me nor have I heard of it working that way anyone I know and trust.  Any time I've ever lost aggro is due to successful FD and waiting for reset.<br /><br />Sometimes, the challenge to reading through these forums is wading through the pure bullshit and getting to the simple truth.  Pre-nerf CoS is insta-invis, that's it.  I've seen no proof that it provides anyone with any special powers (except for maybe the 'pull through' noted above in extruciatingly rare situations).<br /></span></font></td>
